I thank @VetAffairsDems for passing this legislation out of committee recently and will continue to fight for it until it becomes law.   Our veterans and Gold Star families have already sacrificed far too much. We have an obligation to provide them our support.

This additional bill would extend home & automobile leasing protections by allowing the spouses of catastrophically injured servicemembers to terminate property leases and automobile leases, and Gold Star spouses to terminate automobile leases.

It brings me great pride to say this bill was signed into law last year and I hope it will bring some relief to our Gold Star families among difficult times. But this Congress, I introduced a second piece of legislation to take it another step further.

I was honored to have the opportunity to express my gratitude and participate in this ceremony of remembrance – especially as we approach the holiday season and bring the week of Veterans Day to a close. Our Gold Star families have inspired me.

Sen. @ChuckGrassley has been an invaluable partner in the fight to get answers about what happened to Bijan Ghaisar. We’re demanding a DOJ briefing explaining why no charges are being filed against officers who shot and killed an unarmed man.

The Department of Justice's statement explaining why it will not be pursuing federal civil rights criminal charges against the police officers who shot and killed an unarmed man also adds to the long list of unanswered questions that remain, despite a two-year investigation.

The Ghaisar family has experienced so much pain over the last two years, not just in coping with the loss of their beloved son and brother Bijan, but also in trying to understand what led to his death. Today’s announcement will only add to this family’s heartbreak.

It’s heartbreaking to learn of yet another school shooting, this time in Santa Clarita, and I’m keeping this community in my prayers.   The truth is, words alone will not repair the damage done or prevent future tragedies. We must take action to end gun violence. #EnoughIsEnough

column14: Two years after the horrific shooting in Las Vegas, our House majority is committed to #EndGunViolence. We have a epidemic in this country made worse by historic inaction. Las Vegas and El Paso have suffered and I remain devoted to creating safe communities around the country.

After the horrific attack against our community, El Pasoans responded with generosity and donated more than $6M through the One Fund El Paso to support to the victims and families affected by this tragedy.

The numbers are clear. Our economy is not working for most families in Texas and across the country.  It’s time for the @SenateGOP to pass the #RaiseTheWage Act and #PaycheckFairness Act to put more money in the pockets of our workers and address the growing income inequality.

And remember, if you or a veteran you know is dealing with thoughts of suicide, please don’t hesitate, contact the El Paso VA, text the veteran crisis line at 838255 or call the national suicide prevention lifeline at 1-800-273-8255.

To stand with families and friends who have lost immeasurably, to grieve with them, to struggle with them, to try again to pick up the shattered pieces of ourselves in a shared, soulful remembrance.

The first anniversary of any tragedy brings a painful renewal of grief and loss. In these times, even if we think there is nothing more we can say, we come together to remember, to hug, to tell stories and shed tears. And so today our communities gather together once more.

Their faces and voices that night of the first vigil have stayed with me. Thousands had converged to remember the lost, to stand with their friends and loved ones in painful solidarity, to grieve together.

Today marks one year since the fateful October afternoon when 20 souls, beloved by their families, friends & communities, were lost in a terrible limousine crash in Schoharie, New York.   For a year their loved ones have carried the weight of an unfathomable anguish.

The #Schoharie limo crash was the deadliest of its kind, but it was not the first. And if we fail to act, it will not be the last. We owe these families a tremendous debt of action. It’s not just accidental shootings. Over 75 percent of school shootings involve kids and teens having access to unsecured or unsupervised guns at home. And more than 80 percent of guns used by youth in suicide attempts were kept in the home of the victim, a relative, or a friend.

The #PreventFamilyFire Act provides a modest tax credit to incentivize the sale of things like gun safes. If we expand safe storage, we can reduce accidental shootings by 73 percent. It’s that simple.

Every single day, eight kids are killed or injured by unintentional shootings with guns found in the home. We can prevent that by expanding safe storage of firearms. Today, I’m introducing a bipartisan bill to do just that. #PreventFamilyFire  https://t.co/VwYnpIenNk

Alzheimer's impacts millions of families in America and during November we recognize #AlzheimersAwarenessMonth. At the Ways and Means hearing, I highlighted my recent Alzheimer's roundtable, my bill the CHANGE Act, and research efforts to #ENDALZ. WATCH ⬇️  https://t.co/E6w7KiMeEf

Congratulations to former @BGathletics hockey coach, Jerry York, for his induction to the Hockey Hall of Fame! The persistent gender-based wage gap continues to harm women, their families, and the economy. It's time to #CloseTheGap by passing the #PaycheckFairness Act. #LatinaEqualPay  https://t.co/pzYOg1j5nE

Today marks the #TransgenderDayofRemembrance. Too many live in fear, and too many suffer simply for who they are. Every tragedy must remind us of our duty to fight for equality and security for everyone. Join me in committing to continue the struggle.

Gun violence is a tragedy. For every life lost, countless others experience grief, pain and fear. We can do better. We have passed bipartisan legislation to tackle this crisis. The Senate and the president must stop blocking HR 8!

We need to guarantee gender equality once and for all, enshrined at the heart of our Constitution. Proud to see @HouseJudiciary advance legislation this week to help ratify the Equal Rights Amendment this week. #ERAHearing #ERANow

The proposal would limit state standards and attack vulnerable Massachusetts families that rely on these types of benefits, effectively cutting over $100 million annual SNAP dollars.  https://t.co/KesddUrAo6

The DPAA brings American heroes home to their families & communities, fulfilling our country’s pledge to leave no service member behind. I look forward to speaking with @dodpaa Dir. McKeague to ensure they have the necessary resources to continue executing successful operations.

@_WithAnS $35 billion/ year is $100 per year for every man woman and child in this country.  That’s $500 per year of added federal debt (or taxes) for a family of 5. That’s not a small expenditure for most families.  You could send Egypt some more of your $ if you feel it’s valuable.

Thank you @SavannahLMaddox for so eloquently defending liberty in the Kentucky legislature. It’s sad that some of the Republicans there are supporting gun control and opposing fundamental due process rights. #2A

Yet another school shooting. Children shouldn't have to rehearse shooting drills for tragic situations like this. Republicans need to step up to the plate and put the nation's safety above lining their pockets with NRA money.  Our children deserve better. #EndGunViolence

My thoughts and prayers are with the families and communities affected by two more mass killings in America, in Oklahoma and Fresno, CA.    This senseless violence has got to stop! American lives must be the top priority!      https://t.co/IRLOnG9AIV  https://t.co/5AakMQdjOp

San Francisco Mayor George Moscone & Supervisor Harvey Milk embodied the optimistic, progressive vision of our city. 41 years after they were murdered in a shocking act of brutality, we will never stop advancing their mission to bring about a more caring, inclusive future.

Reports that more than 100 protestors have been killed by Iranian security forces raise serious concerns. All Iranians should be able to make their voices heard without fear of reprisal. Iran must immediately restore full internet access and allow all to speak out.

Today, @HouseDemocrats marched to @SenateMajLdr McConnell’s office to demand action to #EndGunViolence.  Thousands of Americans have been killed by guns since the House passed the Bipartisan Background Checks Act more than 265 days ago.  The Senate must hold a vote.  https://t.co/iJVD5TZBw3

.@HouseDemocrats are committed to ensuring that every transgender American can live free from fear and violence, and putting an end to heartbreaking attacks on these brave individuals – particularly those waged against trans women of color.  https://t.co/2VqCrvvruU

Millions of Americans, including @RepEscobar, have seen all that young Dreamers have to offer our country.  Yet it's been more than 160 days since the American Dream & Promise Act passed the House.  @SenateMajLdr McConnell must allow a vote to #ProtectTheDream immediately.  https://t.co/cOg2auYpIQ

We are closely following updates regarding the school shooting in Santa Clarita. Thankful for courageous first responders working to save lives & protect the community. What will it take for Republicans to stop blocking efforts to #EndGunViolence?

In her short time in Washington, @RepEscobar has proven to be a fierce advocate for working families across Texas and the country at large. We all look forward to watching as she continues her work #ForThePeople as Freshman Co-Representative on the House Leadership Team.
American students were shot in their classrooms again today. We are failing our children.  When will the senseless violence end? The Senate must take up House passed gun violence legislation now!

Latina women make 54 cents on the dollar compared to non-Hispanic white men. Latinas and their families can’t afford to wait for the wage gap to close. We urge McConnell and the Senate to pass the #PaycheckFairnessAct. #LatinaEqualPayDay  https://t.co/SHDirLkUQY

My heart breaks for Saugus High School and the Santa Clarita community.   How many more, @senatemajldr Mitch McConnell? Our children cannot keep living like this. The Senate needs to #DoSomething, we need to take action on gun violence.

This #TransDayOfRemembrance, we recognize that the overwhelming majority of murdered transgender people are trans women of color. Today & everyday, we must honor their memory by renewing the fight against bigotry, inequality, & hate. Trans Americans – you are seen & loved! #TDOR
My heart is broken for those killed and those forever changed by this senseless act and I am grateful for the first responders who rushed toward danger to help those hurt.
Another family tragically altered forever, and another community ripped apart by gun violence, this time in Fresno, California.

Today, we pause to remember those killed and those whose lives were forever changed two years ago in the Rancho Tehama Reserve shootings. We continue our work urging the Senate to take up bipartisan bills the House has already passed to help prevent gun violence.

We can't afford to be silent while another school turns into another crime scene. My heart breaks for the victims in Santa Clarita and their family, friends, and classmates.  How many more communities must experience senseless gun violence before we take action? #DoSomething

This is a witch hunt based out of emotion, not out of facts.   As House Democrats ignore policies that actually help American families prosper & remain secure – like #USMCA & supporting our troops – in an attempt to impeach @realdonaldtrump, they are going to walk off the cliff.  https://t.co/ReNKFHgSWo

Forever grateful for my friendship with @OdellCleveland. Your heart for much-needed criminal justice reform is a gift to this community and our country. Thank you for using your voice and efforts to give individuals a second chance. #CJReform  https://t.co/fsroIQamxX

USMCA helps hardworking Americans and their families by establishing strong, updated trade policies with two of our nation’s biggest trading partners—Canada and Mexico. American workers shouldn’t have to wait any longer for these long overdue updates. Congress must pass #USMCAnow  https://t.co/XJcC5bAykq

Serving Arkansas #veterans & their families is a true privilege. Benjamin Haymon recently celebrated his 110th birthday and is considered to be Arkansas's oldest-living #veteran. Delighted my office could organize a celebration of his military service.    https://t.co/4wAOFih3ha  https://t.co/axjcbma4IR

Today we celebrate #family — specifically families that have experienced the joy of #adoption. Loving and welcoming a child in need of a family sends a powerful message about who we are. On #NationalAdoptionDay we support these families and those working to make them a reality.  https://t.co/ueUX9ZyZwN

It's National Veterans & Military Families Month, a time to acknowledge and honor families' sacrificing so much for our nation. Military service truly is a family affair that continues even after retirement. We thank them for supporting their loved ones serving, past and present.  https://t.co/HhJPFRLmst

That violent criminals can be released back into communities due to immigration law loophole reveals our system's brokenness & desperate need of repair. Thanks to @JimInhofe's leadership, our bill protects American families & ensures dangerous illegal immigrants remain detained.

.@CCAInstitute recognizes those strengthening families through supporting foster care and adoption. Proud to have named @thecallinar in Conway & Faulkner Counties as one of AR’s 2019 Angels in Adoption. Every child deserves the love of a family - The Call helps make that happen.  https://t.co/871inySTOb

We have seen the cycle of gun violence play out far too many times - in Santa Clarita, Parkland or Great Mills HS right here in Maryland. Each instance reopens deep wounds in our communities: reminders of the tragic day, of loved-ones lost, and frustration at the lack of action.

Heartbroken by the news of yet another school shooting. My thoughts are with the students of Saugus High School & the Santa Clarita community.  Our children deserve better. We can’t accept this as normal.

W/ the Admin seeking to eliminate this critical funding entirely & make this problem worse, our new proposal will make important investments to reduce the critical repair backlog in public housing and keep families safe. Proud to join @SenKamalaHarris & @SenatorDurbin to intro it

It’s unacceptable that any Illinoisan—that any American—living in public housing finds themselves in units that are crumbling or unsafe. Kids & families rely on investments like these that help improve conditions, increase security & reduce homelessness.  https://t.co/qWba5fPyah

.@USCPSC should take swift action to ban crib bumpers. Allowing crib bumpers to be sold undermines the Commission’s own safe crib guidance that bare is best. So long as @USCPSC fails to act, I’ll work to pass the #SafeCribsAct to protect families in IL and throughout the country

column14: Today, I visited @1800RUNAWAY in Chicago to learn about the important work they’re doing to support runaway youth, teens and their families.  https://t.co/NN0TWLDWEL

Today is #LatinaEqualPay day – signifying that, on average, it will take Latina women all of 2018 and until today to reach the same salary that white men made last year. Latina women need equal pay – families and communities suffer when women are not achieving economic security.  https://t.co/QyS1xfZyKG

There are more than 400,000 youth in foster care across the country. All children belong in loving homes with forever families, which is why I’m proud to cosponsor a resolution recognizing November as #NationalAdoptionMonth.
I was devastated to hear about two more shootings in California over the weekend. The violence and the easy access to guns has to stop. We must start acting now.

On the two-year anniversary of the Rancho Tehama shooting in Northern California, we suffered another shooting today in Santa Clarita. Senate Republicans should step aside and let Congress act. We must do more to stop this mass shooting epidemic.

The problem of high prescription drug costs is felt by too many families in our country.  This #WorldDiabetesDay, we must recommit to passing legislation that supports innovation but also ensures that lifesaving drugs are affordable to the patients who need it.

Today we’re confronted with yet another heartbreaking school shooting. Once again I ask, when will enough be enough? Congress has the ability to reduce these mass shootings. What is lacking is courage among Senate Republicans and the president to actually take action.  https://t.co/PMe8OXqClq
I’m carefully monitoring the shooting at Saugus High School in Santa Clarita. Please comply with all emergency notices.
Be sure to get your flu shot!
